Full Description: Findandremind launched in early 2012. The Command Center is a centralized dashboard with "realtime" Calendar, Message Center, To-do list manager, Group Link manager, and several coordinating functions, including the ability to create/share the following: Private Group home pages (with shared calendar) for private group communication, e-invitations (several design choices and customizing), Volunteer Signup Sheets, Carpool Signup Sheets, Blogs, Photo Albums...all fully integrated into the user's Command Center.  Also, users can join "Open" Groups available on findandremind for their school or church/temple in their area to coordinate within their community. Findandremind's online platform is designed to handle all communications and events for a user's family, friends, activity groups, and organizations (e.g. school, church/temple, associations, etc.) all in one spot, so users reduce "paper shuffling" and can coordinate with each other seamlessly from anywhere. Findandremind works great for any organization, especially those with families as their members...classrooms/schools, churches/temples, sports leagues, associations, non-profits. New services coming soon: Household Helpers - families can search for quality babysitters/nannies, tutors, pet-sitters, housekeepers, handymen, and various other household helpers directly from their Command Center. Mobile platform (iPhone and Android) available in June.

Full Description: A Yale graduate and resident of Boston, Patrycia is both smart and tough. Keeping a health club in perfect operating condition is a hard job and then there can be added pressure being a woman in a male dominated industry. But Patrycia has mastered finding her voice with the perfect balance of tenacity and charm. When it comes to running health clubs efficiently, Patrycia is the best at keeping everything in line. She may be great at running her businesses with an iron fist but Patrycia is by no means cold, she is a very warm and caring person that is also passionate about giving back to the community. With two adorable dogs of her own, Patrycia is an advocate for animal rights and supports the Boston MSPCA regularly. She has also used her health club facilities to host events where the proceeds go to local charities like Hands Across the Sea, Inc. With her consulting company, Trycia helps to manage health club facilities. The fitness club industry is incredibly competitive but Trycia has decades of hands-on experience that sets her above the rest when it comes to giving the best advice to other health club owners. Trycia has helped many clubs increase their profits and boost their clientele. When Trycia helps health clubs thrive, the whole community benefits as it boosts the local economy and enriches the lives of its members. Whether Trycia is helping club owners or organizing charity events, she is always happy to be helping her community.
